{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"rebar-debug Phase 1 COMPLETE — root cause CONFIRMED (3 independent investigators converged + runtime oracle):\n\nMECHANISM (proven by scratch-repo experiment, code-tracer): 'rebar transition' runs 'git commit' at txn.py:268 (STATUS) / 380 (CLAIM). git commit reads HEAD to set the new commit's parent (parse_commit). When HEAD's commit OBJECT is transiently unreadable/missing from the shared .git/objects/, git commit dies with EXACTLY 'fatal: could not parse HEAD' (exit 128); git add does NOT (returns 0). Reproduced verbatim by hiding HEAD's loose object then committing. Ruled out: unborn HEAD (-> root commit, exit 0), truncated HEAD (-> 'not a git repository'). HEAD is always born by transition time (init.py:372-380 commits before the fixture yields). Same runner-FS transient-loose-object fault edf7 fixed on the WRITE side (git add), now on the READ side (git commit parent lookup).\n\nNO CONCURRENCY needed/active (concurrency investigator): async-push gated off (sync.push=always default + no remote), detached enrich-drain gated off (overlap_enabled=False default), repos triple-isolated per xdist worker/test, gc doesn't trigger at ~150-200 loose objs « 6700. (Caveat: gc.autoDetach=true COULD race on the large prod tracker -> same signature as sibling bug a16d; not this isolated test.)\n\nROOT CAUSE (changeable artifact): the transition/claim commit routes through run_git_write -> _with_index_lock_retry (gitutil.py) which retries ONLY index.lock. 'could not parse HEAD' is retried NOWHERE. edf7's fix is doubly out of reach: wrong helper (only event_append._git_add) AND wrong git verb (only add, not commit). LEGITIMACY = defect, cited to the self-heal contract at event_append.py:164-172 ('a transient filesystem hiccup, NOT a data fault ... Retrying ONLY this signature turns a runner-FS blip ... into a self-healed write') and the edf7 comment at :355-359 that named 'could not parse HEAD' but never retried it.\n\nFIX SHAPE (idiomatic, precedented 2x): extend the bounded-retry-on-transient-stderr pattern — add the commit/ref-read signature ('could not parse HEAD' + object-read tree-build siblings) to a transient vocabulary and wrap the COMMIT step in the same retry, centralized on the shared run_git_write/gitutil seam so transition/claim (and create) commits are covered. RED test injects 'fatal: could not parse HEAD' on a transition's first commit and asserts self-heal, mirroring tests/interfaces/store/test_event_append_transient_retry.py. Local repro infeasible (edf7 0/275+, my loop clean) -> RED oracle is injection-based. Moving to Phase 2 (RED->GREEN). Sibling unprotected sites (Step-7 sweep): event_append._git_commit/_git_commit_paths, delete.py, compact.py commits."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784233016524893001,"uuid":"287d56bd-73fd-4220-8686-4d976713fc29"}